[The reservoir of _B. abortus_ is, generally, cattle and of _B. melitensis_, sheep and goats, though cross infections may occur. In fact, cattle may readily be infected also by _B. melitensis_, discharging the bacteria in milk, in most cases without suffering abortions. This phenomenon may have significant public health impact.

_B. abortus_ has been reported from France last time in May 2003, and _B. melitensis in June 2003. Previously, France maintained vaccination policy against _B. melitensis_ and was one of 5 EU Mediterranean member states where activities, supported by the EC, to combat and eradicate _B. melitensis_ were applied.-Mod.AS.



A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1oxc.]
